**2017 Northamptonshire County Council election**

The [2017 Northamptonshire County Council election](2017_United_Kingdom_local_elections) was held on 4 May 2017, as part of the broader [2017 United Kingdom local elections](2017_United_Kingdom_local_elections). This election saw all 57 seats on [Northamptonshire County Council](/Northamptonshire_County_Council) contested. Each [electoral division](/Wards_and_electoral_divisions_of_the_United_Kingdom) returned a single county councillor, elected using the [first-past-the-post voting](/First-past-the-post_voting) system. The elected councillors would serve a four-year term. It's worth noting, with a certain grim inevitability, that these elections were the final ones for [Northamptonshire County Council](/Northamptonshire_County_Council) before its subsequent [dissolution in 2021](/2019%E2%80%932023_structural_changes_to_local_government_in_England). A rather tidy end, wouldn't you agree?

**Navigation**

The navigational elements preceding this article indicate the electoral timeline: the previous election was the [2013 Northamptonshire County Council election](/2013_Northamptonshire_County_Council_election), and the subsequent administrative changes led to elections for [West Northamptonshire Council](/2021_West_Northamptonshire_Council_election) and [North Northamptonshire Council](/2021_North_Northamptonshire_Council_election) in 2021.

**Overall Results Summary**

The election required 29 seats to secure a majority on the council. The turnout was a rather uninspiring 33.4%, a decrease of 2.5 [percentage points](/Percentage_point) from the previous election.

| Party                      | Seats Before Election | Seats Won | Seat Change | Popular Vote | Percentage |
| :------------------------- | :-------------------- | :-------- | :---------- | :----------- | :--------- |
| [Conservative](/Conservative_Party_(UK)) | 36                    | 43        | +7          | 90,813       | 51.1%      |
| [Labour](/Labour_Party_(UK))      | 11                    | 12        | +1          | 49,512       | 27.8%      |
| [Liberal Democrats](/Liberal_Democrats_(UK)) | 6                     | 2         | -4          | 21,777       | 12.2%      |

The [Conservative Party](/Conservative_Party_(UK)) maintained control of the council, securing a stronger majority than they held previously. The [Labour Party](/Labour_Party_(UK)) saw a slight increase in their representation, while the [Liberal Democrats](/Liberal_Democrats_(UK)) experienced a notable loss of seats.

